latestPosts.caption: Amidst the rugged beauty of Ladakh’s Aryan Valley lies a lesser-known gem: the Brokpa community. Clad in vibrant attire and floral crowns, the Brokpas stand as living testaments to an ancient lineage, believed by some to descend from Alexander the Great’s army. I had the rare privilege to photograph these enigmatic people. Amidst this tapestry, I found myself a silent observer, threading the fragile line between intruder and guest. The Brokpas, with their age-old wisdom, subsist on apricots;a sweet secret they believe keeps time at bay. As I navigated the intricacies of their daily life, an impromptu dance lesson found my urban agility hilariously unmatched to their graceful traditional moves. The Brokpas aren’t just a community, they’re a bridge between epochs, and I was fortunate to tread that bridge, if only for a moment.

latestPosts.caption:
Not long ago, When @akshatbansal__ , @samar.rajput05 , and I first got together for this project @shehar_in , we didn’t expect it to turn into such a wild and beautiful ride. From crisscrossing Hisar for two days to scout locations, to Akshat’s car getting  smashed by an overenthusiastic farmer on a tractor, to somehow getting an entire village to dance — this campaign became one fun adventure.
We spent nearly a month building it, with several days of shooting. And even though it wasn’t all that long ago… has the notion of time changed? Just wondering — everything these days seems to be packed into a single day!
Big ups once again to the amazing crew — @eshwarlog @kawaiiiichan_ , @bharath_bharath_11 , @a_karki15 , and @amit_eapen — for making it all happen.
